<subSubSection box="[312,1323,1399,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,359,1625]" box="[312,1323,1399,1425]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[312,435,1399,1424]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Etymology</emphasis>
. The specific epithet “ 
<taxonomicName box="[697,790,1399,1425]" class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Sialis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="elegans">elegans</taxonomicName>
” refers to the elegant appearance of the adult.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[264,1323,359,1625]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis box="[312,422,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">Remarks.</emphasis>
The new species seems to be closely related to 
<taxonomicName box="[1014,1185,1439,1464]" class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Sialis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicoloris" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[1014,1185,1439,1464]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">S. versicoloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[1196,1289,1439,1465]" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
in having an orange pronotum, but it can be separated from 
<taxonomicName box="[961,1131,1479,1504]" class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Sialis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicoloris">
<emphasis box="[961,1131,1479,1504]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">S. versicoloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by the strongly sclerotized terminal plate, the simply hooked genital plate, and the lateral plate distinctly produced backward. In 
<taxonomicName box="[545,713,1559,1584]" class="Insecta" family="Sialidae" genus="Sialis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Megaloptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="27" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="versicoloris">
<emphasis box="[545,713,1559,1584]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="27">S. versicoloris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the terminal plate is feebly sclerotized, the genital plate is more complicated, and the lateral plate is produced dorsally.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
